        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:2:17:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/17/2",
        "text": [
          " «إِنْ كَانَ مَعَهُ قَوْمٌ يَخْشَى أَنْ يَحْبِسَهُمْ عَنْ عَشَائِهِمْ فَلْيُفْطِرْ مَعَهُمْ وَ إِنْ كَانَ غَيْرُ ذَلِكَ فَلْيُصَلِّ ثُمَّ لْيُفْطِرْ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.1933 - Al-Halabi narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) that he was asked about breaking the fast before or after prayer.\nImam (as) said: \"If he is with a group and fears delaying their dinner, let him break his fast with them. Otherwise, let him pray first, then break his fast.\""
          ]
        }
      }
